{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":225,"text":"America's public energy conversation"},{"time":2487,"text":"boils down to this question:"},{"time":4710,"text":"Would you rather die of A) oil wars,"},{"time":8090,"text":"or B) climate change,"},{"time":10700,"text":"or C) nuclear holocaust,"},{"time":12100,"text":"or D) all of the above?"},{"time":15400,"text":"Oh, I missed one: or E) none of the above?"},{"time":18200,"text":"That's the one we're not normally offered."},{"time":20315,"text":"What if we could make energy do our work"},{"time":22454,"text":"without working our undoing?"},{"time":24900,"text":"Could we have fuel without fear?"},{"time":27000,"text":"Could we reinvent fire?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":29408,"text":"You see, fire made us human;"},{"time":31038,"text":"fossil fuels made us modern."},{"time":33092,"text":"But now we need a new fire"},{"time":34392,"text":"that makes us safe, secure, healthy and durable."},{"time":37915,"text":"Let's see how."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40174,"text":"Four-fifths of the world's energy"},{"time":43060,"text":"still comes from burning each year"},{"time":44833,"text":"four cubic miles of the rotted remains"},{"time":48333,"text":"of primeval swamp goo."},{"time":50933,"text":"Those fossil fuels"},{"time":53067,"text":"have built our civilization."},{"time":56144,"text":"They've created our wealth."},{"time":58229,"text":"They've enriched the lives of billions."},{"time":59805,"text":"But they also have rising costs"},{"time":62444,"text":"to our security, economy, health and environment"},{"time":66833,"text":"that are starting to erode, if not outweigh their benefits."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70087,"text":"So we need a new fire."},{"time":72329,"text":"And switching from the old fire to the new fire"},{"time":75231,"text":"means changing two big stories about oil and electricity,"},{"time":79267,"text":"each of which puts two-fifths of the fossil carbon in the air."},{"time":83944,"text":"But they're really quite distinct."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85913,"text":"Less than one percent of our electricity is made from oil --"},{"time":89325,"text":"although almost half is made from coal."},{"time":93029,"text":"Their uses are quite concentrated."},{"time":95308,"text":"Three-fourths of our oil fuel is transportation."},{"time":98048,"text":"Three-fourths of our electricity powers buildings."},{"time":100823,"text":"And the rest of both runs factories."},{"time":102864,"text":"So very efficient vehicles, buildings and factories"},{"time":106700,"text":"save oil and coal,"},{"time":108469,"text":"and also natural gas that can displace both of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111900,"text":"But today's energy system is not just inefficient,"},{"time":115585,"text":"it is also disconnected,"},{"time":117592,"text":"aging, dirty and insecure."},{"time":120300,"text":"So it needs refurbishment."},{"time":122777,"text":"By 2050 though, it could become efficient,"},{"time":126205,"text":"connected and distributed"},{"time":129467,"text":"with elegantly frugal"},{"time":130867,"text":"autos, factories and buildings"},{"time":133600,"text":"all relying on a modern, secure"},{"time":135967,"text":"and resilient electricity system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138629,"text":"We can eliminate our addiction to oil and coal by 2050"},{"time":144067,"text":"and use one-third less natural gas"},{"time":147236,"text":"while switching to efficient use"},{"time":150121,"text":"and renewable supply."},{"time":152705,"text":"This could cost, by 2050,"},{"time":156238,"text":"five trillion dollars less in net present value,"},{"time":159490,"text":"that is expressed as a lump sum today,"},{"time":162133,"text":"than business as usual --"},{"time":163679,"text":"assuming that carbon emissions"},{"time":165133,"text":"and all other hidden or external costs are worth zero --"},{"time":168198,"text":"a conservatively low estimate."},{"time":172082,"text":"Yet this cheaper energy system"},{"time":174033,"text":"could support 158 percent bigger U.S. economy"},{"time":177867,"text":"all without needing oil or coal,"},{"time":180236,"text":"or for that matter nuclear energy."},{"time":182700,"text":"Moreover, this transition needs no new inventions"},{"time":185723,"text":"and no acts of Congress"},{"time":188985,"text":"and no new federal taxes, mandate subsidies or laws"},{"time":193467,"text":"and running Washington gridlock."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196418,"text":"Let me say that again."},{"time":197333,"text":"I'm going to tell you how to get the United States"},{"time":200102,"text":"completely off oil and coal, five trillion dollars cheaper"},{"time":203413,"text":"with no act of Congress"},{"time":204759,"text":"led by business for profit."},{"time":207269,"text":"In other words, we're going to use our most effective institutions --"},{"time":210908,"text":"private enterprise co-evolving with civil society"},{"time":214721,"text":"and sped by military innovation"},{"time":217233,"text":"to go around our least effective institutions."},{"time":220033,"text":"And whether you care most"},{"time":222367,"text":"about profits and jobs and competitive advantage"},{"time":225798,"text":"or national security, or environmental stewardship"},{"time":228208,"text":"and climate protection and public health,"},{"time":230369,"text":"reinventing fire makes sense and makes money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234652,"text":"General Eisenhower reputedly said"},{"time":238098,"text":"that enlarging the boundaries of a tough problem"},{"time":240718,"text":"makes it soluble by encompassing more options and more synergies."},{"time":245287,"text":"So in reinventing fire,"},{"time":246956,"text":"we integrated all four sectors that use energy --"},{"time":250123,"text":"transportation, buildings, industry and electricity --"},{"time":253762,"text":"and we integrated four kinds of innovation,"},{"time":256385,"text":"not just technology and policy,"},{"time":258933,"text":"but also design and business strategy."},{"time":262033,"text":"Those combinations yield"},{"time":264048,"text":"very much more than the sum of the parts,"},{"time":266154,"text":"especially in creating deeply disruptive business opportunities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271500,"text":"Oil costs our economy two billion dollars a day,"},{"time":275548,"text":"plus another four billion dollars a day"},{"time":277915,"text":"in hidden economic and military costs,"},{"time":280562,"text":"raising its total cost to over a sixth of GDP."},{"time":284492,"text":"Our mobility fuel goes three-fifths to automobiles."},{"time":287036,"text":"So let's start by making autos oil free."},{"time":289682,"text":"Two-thirds of the energy it takes to move a typical car"},{"time":292862,"text":"is caused by its weight."},{"time":295064,"text":"And every unit of energy you save at the wheels,"},{"time":298571,"text":"by taking out weight or drag,"},{"time":299818,"text":"saves seven units in the tank,"},{"time":301848,"text":"because you don't have to waste six units"},{"time":303533,"text":"getting the energy to the wheels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305633,"text":"Unfortunately, over the past quarter century,"},{"time":309218,"text":"epidemic obesity has made our two-ton steel cars"},{"time":311933,"text":"gain weight twice as fast as we have."},{"time":315756,"text":"But today, ultralight, ultrastrong materials,"},{"time":319410,"text":"like carbon fiber composites,"},{"time":321995,"text":"can make dramatic weight savings snowball"},{"time":324367,"text":"and can make cars simpler and cheaper to build."},{"time":328282,"text":"Lighter and more slippery autos"},{"time":330648,"text":"need less force to move them,"},{"time":332895,"text":"so their engines get smaller."},{"time":335169,"text":"Indeed, that sort of vehicle fitness"},{"time":338000,"text":"then makes electric propulsion affordable"},{"time":341167,"text":"because the batteries or fuel cells"},{"time":344300,"text":"also get smaller and lighter and cheaper."},{"time":347900,"text":"So sticker prices will ultimately fall to about the same as today,"},{"time":351800,"text":"while the driving cost, even from the start,"},{"time":355321,"text":"is very much lower."}]},{"cues":[{"time":357069,"text":"So these innovations together can transform automakers"},{"time":361215,"text":"from wringing tiny savings"},{"time":363577,"text":"out of Victorian engine and seal-stamping technologies"},{"time":366908,"text":"to the steeply falling costs"},{"time":369646,"text":"of three linked innovations that strongly reenforce each other --"},{"time":374746,"text":"namely ultralight materials, making them into structures"},{"time":378669,"text":"and electric propulsion."},{"time":381000,"text":"The sales can grow and the prices fall even faster"},{"time":385700,"text":"with temporary feebates,"},{"time":387408,"text":"that is rebates for efficient new autos"},{"time":389662,"text":"paid for by fees on inefficient ones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392762,"text":"And just in the first two years"},{"time":395608,"text":"the biggest of Europe's five feebate programs"},{"time":399056,"text":"has tripled the speed of improving automotive efficiency."},{"time":403102,"text":"The resulting shift to electric autos"},{"time":406531,"text":"is going to be as game-changing"},{"time":408002,"text":"as shifting from typewriters to the gains in computers."},{"time":412200,"text":"Of course, computers and electronics"},{"time":414300,"text":"are now America's biggest industry,"},{"time":416600,"text":"while typewriter makers have vanished."},{"time":418754,"text":"So vehicle fitness"},{"time":420675,"text":"opens a new automotive competitive strategy"},{"time":424244,"text":"that can double the oil savings over the next 40 years,"},{"time":427498,"text":"but then also make electrification affordable,"},{"time":430375,"text":"and that displaces the rest of the oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434359,"text":"America could lead this next automotive revolution."},{"time":437915,"text":"Currently the leader is Germany."},{"time":440400,"text":"Last year, Volkswagen announced"},{"time":442908,"text":"that by next year they'll be producing"},{"time":445131,"text":"this carbon fiber plugin hybrid"},{"time":448000,"text":"getting 230 miles a gallon."},{"time":450408,"text":"Also last year, BMW announced"},{"time":452923,"text":"this carbon fiber electric car,"},{"time":455192,"text":"they said that its carbon fiber is paid for"},{"time":457167,"text":"by needing fewer batteries."},{"time":459221,"text":"And they said, \"We do not intend to be a typewriter maker.\""},{"time":461767,"text":"Audi claimed it's going to beat them both by a year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465275,"text":"Seven years ago, an even faster and cheaper"},{"time":468500,"text":"American manufacturing technology"},{"time":471092,"text":"was used to make this little carbon fiber test part,"},{"time":478536,"text":"which doubles as a carbon cap."},{"time":480875,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":482438,"text":"In one minute -- and you can tell from the sound"},{"time":485500,"text":"how immensely stiff and strong it is."},{"time":488333,"text":"Don't worry about dropping it, it's tougher than titanium."},{"time":491825,"text":"Tom Friedman actually whacked it as hard as he could with a sledgehammer"},{"time":494048,"text":"without even scuffing it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495587,"text":"But such manufacturing techniques"},{"time":497702,"text":"can scale to automotive speed and cost"},{"time":500925,"text":"with aerospace performance."},{"time":502379,"text":"They can save four-fifths of the capital needed to make autos."},{"time":505900,"text":"They can save lives"},{"time":507062,"text":"because this stuff can absorb"},{"time":508354,"text":"up to 12 times as much crash energy per pound as steel."},{"time":511618,"text":"If we made all of our autos this way,"},{"time":513367,"text":"it would save oil equivalent to finding"},{"time":516290,"text":"one and a half Saudi Arabias, or half an OPEC,"},{"time":519122,"text":"by drilling in the Detroit formation, a very prospective play."},{"time":523554,"text":"And all those mega-barrels under Detroit"},{"time":526254,"text":"cost an average of 18 bucks a barrel."},{"time":528767,"text":"They are all-American, carbon-free"},{"time":530613,"text":"and inexhaustible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532933,"text":"The same physics and the same business logic"},{"time":535687,"text":"also apply to big vehicles."},{"time":537233,"text":"In the five years ending with 2010,"},{"time":539925,"text":"Walmart saved 60 percent of the fuel per ton-mile"},{"time":544500,"text":"in its giant fleet of heavy trucks"},{"time":545900,"text":"through better logistics and design."},{"time":547300,"text":"But just the technological savings in heavy trucks"},{"time":550315,"text":"can get to two-thirds."},{"time":552200,"text":"And combined with triple to quintuple efficiency airplanes,"},{"time":555487,"text":"now on the drawing board,"},{"time":557208,"text":"can save close to a trillion dollars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":559454,"text":"Also today's military revolution in energy efficiency"},{"time":563823,"text":"is going to speed up all of these civilian advances"},{"time":566800,"text":"in much the same way that military R&amp;D"},{"time":569329,"text":"has given us the Internet, the Global Positioning System"},{"time":572523,"text":"and the jet engine and microchip industries."},{"time":575592,"text":"As we design and build vehicles better,"},{"time":579115,"text":"we can also use them smarter"},{"time":581215,"text":"by harnessing four powerful techniques"},{"time":583462,"text":"for eliminating needless driving."},{"time":585454,"text":"Instead of just seeing the travel grow,"},{"time":588246,"text":"we can use innovative pricing,"},{"time":590900,"text":"charging for road infrastructure by the mile, not by the gallon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594854,"text":"We can use some smart IT to enhance transit"},{"time":598100,"text":"and enable car sharing and ride sharing."},{"time":601641,"text":"We can allow smart and lucrative growth models"},{"time":605900,"text":"that help people already be near where they want to be,"},{"time":610077,"text":"so they don't need to go somewhere else."},{"time":611590,"text":"And we can use smart IT"},{"time":613700,"text":"to make traffic free-flowing."},{"time":616252,"text":"Together, those things can give us the same or better access"},{"time":619067,"text":"with 46 to 84 percent less driving,"},{"time":623567,"text":"saving another 0.4 trillion dollars,"},{"time":626205,"text":"plus 0.3 trillion dollars from using trucks more productively."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631200,"text":"So 40 years hence, when you add it all up,"},{"time":633905,"text":"a far more mobile U.S. economy"},{"time":636913,"text":"can use no oil."},{"time":638992,"text":"Saving or displacing barrels for 25 bucks"},{"time":642500,"text":"rather than buying them for over a hundred,"},{"time":643900,"text":"adds up to a $4 trillion net saving"},{"time":647675,"text":"counting all the hidden costs at zero."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650682,"text":"So to get mobility without oil,"},{"time":653600,"text":"to phase out the oil,"},{"time":655700,"text":"we can get efficient and then switch fuels."},{"time":659131,"text":"Those 125 to 240 mile-per-gallon-equivalent autos"},{"time":663475,"text":"can use any mixture of hydrogen fuel cells,"},{"time":667318,"text":"electricity and advanced biofuels."},{"time":670429,"text":"The trucks and planes can realistically use"},{"time":674082,"text":"hydrogen or advanced biofuels."},{"time":676902,"text":"The trucks could even use natural gas."},{"time":678967,"text":"But no vehicles will need oil."},{"time":680967,"text":"And the most biofuel we might need,"},{"time":684052,"text":"just three million barrels a day,"},{"time":685795,"text":"can be made two-thirds from waste"},{"time":687433,"text":"without displacing any cropland"},{"time":689267,"text":"and without harming soil or climate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692300,"text":"Our team speeds up these kinds of oil savings"},{"time":694315,"text":"by what we call \"institutional acupuncture.\""},{"time":697267,"text":"We figure out where the business logic"},{"time":698667,"text":"is congested and not flowing properly,"},{"time":701136,"text":"we stick little needles in it to get it flowing,"},{"time":702948,"text":"working with partners like Ford and Walmart and the Pentagon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705441,"text":"And the long transition is already well under way."},{"time":708902,"text":"In fact, three years ago mainstream analysts were starting to see peak oil,"},{"time":713205,"text":"not in supply, but in demand."},{"time":716152,"text":"And Deutsche Bank even said world oil use could peak around 2016."}]},{"cues":[{"time":721264,"text":"In other words, oil is getting uncompetitive even at low prices"},{"time":725925,"text":"before it becomes unavailable even at high prices."},{"time":730018,"text":"But the electrified vehicles"},{"time":732944,"text":"don't need to burden the electricity grid."},{"time":735721,"text":"Rather, when smart autos exchange electricity and information"},{"time":739156,"text":"through smart buildings with smart grids,"},{"time":741582,"text":"they're adding to the grid valuable flexibility and storage"},{"time":744898,"text":"that help the grid integrate"},{"time":746748,"text":"varying solar and wind power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":749595,"text":"So the electrified autos"},{"time":751271,"text":"make the auto and electricity problems"},{"time":753895,"text":"easier to solve together than separately."},{"time":756133,"text":"And they also converge the oil story"},{"time":757964,"text":"with our second big story,"},{"time":760548,"text":"saving electricity and then making it differently."},{"time":764308,"text":"And those twin revolutions in electricity"},{"time":767290,"text":"will bring to that sector"},{"time":770344,"text":"more numerous and profound and diverse disruptions"},{"time":773129,"text":"than any other sector,"},{"time":774490,"text":"because we've got 21st century technology and speed colliding head-on"},{"time":778705,"text":"with 20th and 19th century institutions, rules and cultures."},{"time":783400,"text":"Changing how we make electricity gets easier"},{"time":786475,"text":"if we need less of it."},{"time":788990,"text":"Most of it now is wasted"},{"time":790652,"text":"and the technologies for saving it"},{"time":792633,"text":"keep improving faster than we're installing them."},{"time":795587,"text":"So the unbought efficiency resource"},{"time":798033,"text":"keeps getting ever bigger and cheaper."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800933,"text":"But as efficiency in buildings and industry"},{"time":803995,"text":"starts to grow faster than the economy,"},{"time":805967,"text":"America's electricity use could actually shrink,"},{"time":810390,"text":"even with the little extra use required"},{"time":813987,"text":"for those efficient electrified autos."},{"time":815967,"text":"And we can do this just by reasonably accelerating existing trends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":820795,"text":"Over the next 40 years, buildings,"},{"time":823133,"text":"which use three-quarters of the electricity,"},{"time":825341,"text":"can triple or quadruple their energy productivity,"},{"time":829175,"text":"saving 1.4 trillion dollars, net present value,"},{"time":833100,"text":"with a 33 percent internal rate of return"},{"time":836700,"text":"or in English,"},{"time":838371,"text":"the savings are worth four times what they cost."},{"time":841567,"text":"And industry can accelerate too,"},{"time":843805,"text":"doubling its energy productivity"},{"time":845521,"text":"with a 21 percent internal rate of return."},{"time":848469,"text":"The key is a disruptive innovation"},{"time":850508,"text":"that we call integrative design"},{"time":853331,"text":"that often makes very big energy savings"},{"time":856259,"text":"cost less than small or no savings."},{"time":858736,"text":"That is, it can give you expanding returns,"},{"time":861364,"text":"not diminishing returns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":863218,"text":"That is how our 2010 retrofit"},{"time":866964,"text":"is saving over two-fifths of the energy in the Empire State Building --"},{"time":870167,"text":"remanufacturing those six and a half thousand windows on site"},{"time":874321,"text":"into super windows that pass light, but reflect heat."},{"time":878633,"text":"plus better lights and office equipment and such"},{"time":881818,"text":"cut the maximum cooling load by a third."},{"time":885433,"text":"And then renovating smaller chillers instead of adding bigger ones"},{"time":890500,"text":"saved 17 million dollars of"},{"time":892023,"text":"capital cost, which helped pay for the other improvements"},{"time":895400,"text":"and reduce the payback to just three years."},{"time":899444,"text":"Integrative design can also increase"},{"time":901667,"text":"energy savings in industry."},{"time":903875,"text":"Dow's billion-dollar efficiency investment"},{"time":905867,"text":"has already returned nine billion dollars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":909167,"text":"But industry as a whole has another half-trillion dollars"},{"time":912113,"text":"of energy still to save."},{"time":914308,"text":"For example, three-fifths of the world's electricity runs motors."},{"time":918867,"text":"Half of that runs pumps and fans."},{"time":920936,"text":"And those can all be made more efficient,"},{"time":923810,"text":"and the motors that turn them"},{"time":925525,"text":"can have their system efficiency roughly doubled"},{"time":929175,"text":"by integrating 35 improvements, paying back in about a year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933090,"text":"But first we ought to be capturing bigger, cheaper savings"},{"time":936318,"text":"that are normally ignored and are not in the textbooks."},{"time":938967,"text":"For example, pumps, the biggest use of motors,"},{"time":942121,"text":"move liquid through pipes."},{"time":943938,"text":"But a standard industrial pumping loop"},{"time":945738,"text":"was redesigned to use at least 86 percent less energy,"},{"time":950115,"text":"not by getting better pumps,"},{"time":952054,"text":"but just by replacing long, thin, crooked pipes"},{"time":955436,"text":"with fat, short, straight pipes."},{"time":958052,"text":"This is not about new technology,"},{"time":961267,"text":"it's just rearranging our metal furniture."},{"time":963244,"text":"Of course, it also shrinks the pumping equipment"},{"time":965598,"text":"and its capital costs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":967313,"text":"So what do such savings mean"},{"time":969933,"text":"for the electricity that is three-fifths used in motors?"},{"time":973615,"text":"Well, from the coal burned at the power plant"},{"time":976715,"text":"through all these compounding losses,"},{"time":979836,"text":"only a tenth of the fuel energy"},{"time":982659,"text":"actually ends up coming out the pipe as flow."},{"time":985659,"text":"But now let's turn those compounding losses around backwards,"},{"time":989333,"text":"and every unit of flow or friction that we save in the pipe"},{"time":994964,"text":"saves 10 units of fuel cost, pollution"},{"time":999108,"text":"and what Hunter Lovins calls \"global weirding\""},{"time":1001731,"text":"back at the power plant."},{"time":1003133,"text":"And of course, as you go back upstream,"},{"time":1004825,"text":"the components get smaller and therefore cheaper."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1008125,"text":"Our team has lately found such snowballing energy savings"},{"time":1012705,"text":"in more than 30 billion dollars worth of industrial redesigns --"},{"time":1015938,"text":"everything from data centers and chip fabs"},{"time":1018667,"text":"to mines and refineries."},{"time":1020859,"text":"Typically our retrofit designs"},{"time":1022300,"text":"save about 30 to 60 percent of the energy"},{"time":1025254,"text":"and pay back in a few years,"},{"time":1027200,"text":"while the new facility designs save 40 to 90-odd percent"},{"time":1031369,"text":"with generally lower capital cost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1033800,"text":"Now needing less electricity"},{"time":1036864,"text":"would ease and speed"},{"time":1039179,"text":"the shift to new sources of electricity, chiefly renewables."},{"time":1042341,"text":"China leads their explosive growth and their plummeting cost."},{"time":1046825,"text":"In fact, these solar power module costs"},{"time":1050246,"text":"have just fallen off the bottom of the chart."},{"time":1052625,"text":"And Germany now has more solar workers"},{"time":1055695,"text":"than America has steel workers."},{"time":1058333,"text":"Already in about 20 states"},{"time":1060179,"text":"private installers will come"},{"time":1062533,"text":"put those cheap solar cells on your roof with no money down"},{"time":1066018,"text":"and beat your utility bill."},{"time":1067887,"text":"Such unregulated products"},{"time":1070079,"text":"could ultimately add up to a virtual utility"},{"time":1072933,"text":"that bypasses your electric company"},{"time":1075887,"text":"just as your cellphone bypassed your wireline phone company."},{"time":1079718,"text":"And this sort of thing gives utility executives the heebee-jeebees"},{"time":1083136,"text":"and it gives venture capitalists sweet dreams."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1085359,"text":"Renewables are no longer a fringe activity."},{"time":1088452,"text":"For each of the past four years"},{"time":1090929,"text":"half of the world's new generating capacity"},{"time":1093767,"text":"has been renewable,"},{"time":1095364,"text":"mainly lately in developing countries."},{"time":1097056,"text":"In 2010, renewables other than big hydro,"},{"time":1101348,"text":"particularly wind and solar cells,"},{"time":1103679,"text":"got 151 billion dollars of private investment,"},{"time":1108671,"text":"and they actually surpassed the total installed capacity"},{"time":1111256,"text":"of nuclear power in the world"},{"time":1112941,"text":"by adding 60 billion watts in that one year."},{"time":1116400,"text":"That happens to be the same amount of solar cell capacity"},{"time":1120100,"text":"that the world can now make every year --"},{"time":1122915,"text":"a number that goes up 60 or 70 percent a year."},{"time":1126262,"text":"In contrast, the net additions of nuclear capacity and coal capacity"},{"time":1131795,"text":"and the orders behind those keep fading"},{"time":1135364,"text":"because they cost too much and they have too much financial risk."},{"time":1137900,"text":"In fact in this country,"},{"time":1139300,"text":"no new nuclear power plant"},{"time":1141415,"text":"has been able to raise any private construction capital,"},{"time":1143933,"text":"despite seven years of 100-plus percent subsidies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1148348,"text":"So how else could we replace the coal-fired power plants?"},{"time":1152352,"text":"Well efficiency and gas can displace them all"},{"time":1156121,"text":"at just below their operating cost"},{"time":1158805,"text":"and, combined with renewables, can displace them more than 23 times"},{"time":1162559,"text":"at less than their replacement cost."},{"time":1164633,"text":"But we only need to replace them once."},{"time":1166641,"text":"We're often told though"},{"time":1169329,"text":"that only coal and nuclear plants can keep the lights on,"},{"time":1171710,"text":"because they're 24/7,"},{"time":1172995,"text":"whereas wind and solar power are variable,"},{"time":1175818,"text":"and hence supposedly unreliable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1178833,"text":"Actually no generator is 24/7. They all break."},{"time":1182218,"text":"And when a big plant goes down,"},{"time":1184333,"text":"you lose a thousand megawatts in milliseconds,"},{"time":1187125,"text":"often for weeks or months, often without warning."},{"time":1190618,"text":"That is exactly why we've designed the grid"},{"time":1192615,"text":"to back up failed plants with working plants."},{"time":1196885,"text":"And in exactly the same way,"},{"time":1198615,"text":"the grid can handle wind and solar power's"},{"time":1203646,"text":"forecastable variations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1206195,"text":"Hourly simulations"},{"time":1209502,"text":"show that largely or wholly renewable grids"},{"time":1213269,"text":"can deliver highly reliable power"},{"time":1215046,"text":"when they're forecasted,"},{"time":1216675,"text":"integrated and diversified"},{"time":1218729,"text":"by both type and location."},{"time":1220782,"text":"And that's true both for continental areas like the U.S. or Europe"},{"time":1225005,"text":"and for smaller areas embedded within a larger grid."},{"time":1229490,"text":"That is how, for example,"},{"time":1231129,"text":"four German states in 2010"},{"time":1233513,"text":"were 43 to 52 percent wind powered."},{"time":1236125,"text":"Portugal was 45 percent renewable powered,"},{"time":1239767,"text":"Denmark 36."},{"time":1242092,"text":"And it's how all of Europe can shift"},{"time":1245377,"text":"to renewable electricity."},{"time":1246662,"text":"In America, our aging, dirty and insecure power system"},{"time":1251387,"text":"has to be replaced anyway by 2050."},{"time":1254271,"text":"And whatever we replace it with"},{"time":1255898,"text":"is going to cost about the same,"},{"time":1257336,"text":"about six trillion dollars at present value --"},{"time":1260046,"text":"whether we buy more of what we've got"},{"time":1262254,"text":"or new nuclear and so-called clean coal,"},{"time":1264367,"text":"or renewables that are more or less centralized."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1267998,"text":"But those four futures at the same cost"},{"time":1271267,"text":"differ profoundly in their risks,"},{"time":1273336,"text":"around national security,"},{"time":1275867,"text":"fuel, water, finance, technology,"},{"time":1279405,"text":"climate and health."},{"time":1280936,"text":"For example, our over-centralized grid"},{"time":1283771,"text":"is very vulnerable to cascading"},{"time":1287702,"text":"and potentially economy-shattering blackouts"},{"time":1290429,"text":"caused by bad space weather or other natural disasters"},{"time":1293867,"text":"or a terrorist attack."},{"time":1295813,"text":"But that blackout risk disappears,"},{"time":1298544,"text":"and all of the other risks are best managed,"},{"time":1300536,"text":"with distributed renewables"},{"time":1302790,"text":"organized into local micro-grids that normally interconnect,"},{"time":1307067,"text":"but can stand alone at need."},{"time":1308875,"text":"That is, they can disconnect fractally"},{"time":1310913,"text":"and then reconnect seamlessly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1313767,"text":"That approach is exactly what the Pentagon is adopting"},{"time":1317044,"text":"for its own power supply."},{"time":1318359,"text":"They think they need that; how about the rest of us that they're defending?"},{"time":1321625,"text":"We want our stuff to work too."},{"time":1323325,"text":"At about the same cost as business as usual,"},{"time":1326895,"text":"this would maximize national security,"},{"time":1328900,"text":"customer choice, entrepreneurial opportunity"},{"time":1332902,"text":"and innovation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1334525,"text":"Together, efficient use and diverse dispersed renewable supply"},{"time":1340200,"text":"are starting to transform the whole electricity sector."},{"time":1343123,"text":"Traditionally utilities build"},{"time":1344754,"text":"a lot of giant coal and nuclear plants"},{"time":1346923,"text":"and a bunch of big gas plants"},{"time":1348869,"text":"and maybe a little bit of efficiency renewables."},{"time":1349938,"text":"And those utilities were rewarded,"},{"time":1352467,"text":"as they still are in 34 states,"},{"time":1354921,"text":"for selling you more electricity."},{"time":1358387,"text":"However, especially where regulators"},{"time":1361185,"text":"are now instead rewarding cutting your bills,"},{"time":1364738,"text":"the investments are shifting radically"},{"time":1368521,"text":"toward efficiency, demand response, cogeneration,"},{"time":1371052,"text":"renewables and ways to knit them all together reliably"},{"time":1374421,"text":"with less transmission"},{"time":1375844,"text":"and little or no bulk electricity storage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1378698,"text":"So our energy future is not fate, but choice,"},{"time":1381525,"text":"and that choice is very flexible."},{"time":1384271,"text":"In 1976, for example,"},{"time":1385871,"text":"government and industry insisted"},{"time":1387695,"text":"that the amount of energy needed to make a dollar of GDP"},{"time":1390279,"text":"could never go down."},{"time":1392062,"text":"And I heretically suggested it could go down several-fold."},{"time":1395692,"text":"Well that's what's actually happened so far."},{"time":1397956,"text":"It's fallen by half."},{"time":1399271,"text":"But with today's much better technologies,"},{"time":1401762,"text":"more mature delivery channels and integrative design,"},{"time":1404671,"text":"we can do far more and even cheaper."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1408571,"text":"So to solve the energy problem,"},{"time":1411079,"text":"we just needed to enlarge it."},{"time":1413000,"text":"And the results may at first seem incredible,"},{"time":1416200,"text":"but as Marshall McLuhan said,"},{"time":1417977,"text":"\"Only puny secrets need protection."},{"time":1420729,"text":"Big discoveries are protected by public incredulity.\""},{"time":1426813,"text":"Now combine the electricity and oil revolutions,"},{"time":1430295,"text":"both driven by modern efficiency,"},{"time":1431979,"text":"and you get the really big story: reinventing fire,"},{"time":1435521,"text":"where business enabled and sped by smart policies in mindful markets"},{"time":1440652,"text":"can lead the United States completely off oil and coal by 2050,"},{"time":1445182,"text":"saving 5 trillion dollars,"},{"time":1447502,"text":"growing the economy 2.6-fold,"},{"time":1450095,"text":"strengthening out national security,"},{"time":1451738,"text":"oh, and by the way, by getting rid of the oil and coal,"},{"time":1454723,"text":"reducing the fossil carbon emissions by 82 to 86 percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1459233,"text":"Now if you like any of those outcomes,"},{"time":1462567,"text":"you can support reinventing fire"},{"time":1464759,"text":"without needing to like all of them"},{"time":1466621,"text":"and without needing to agree about which of them is most important."},{"time":1470044,"text":"So focusing on outcomes, not motives,"},{"time":1473121,"text":"can turn gridlock and conflict"},{"time":1475677,"text":"into a unifying solution to America's energy challenge."},{"time":1479979,"text":"This also turns out to be the best way"},{"time":1483036,"text":"to cope with global challenges --"},{"time":1485536,"text":"climate change, nuclear proliferation,"},{"time":1488115,"text":"energy insecurity, energy poverty --"},{"time":1490546,"text":"all of which make us less safe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1494192,"text":"Now our team at RMI helps smart companies"},{"time":1497879,"text":"to get unstuck and speed this journey"},{"time":1500948,"text":"via six sectoral initiatives, with some more hatching."},{"time":1504010,"text":"Of course there's still a lot of old thinking out there too."},{"time":1506967,"text":"Former oil man Maurice Strong said,"},{"time":1510144,"text":"\"Not all the fossils are in the fuel.\""},{"time":1512090,"text":"But as Edgar Woolard, who used to chair Dupont, reminds us,"},{"time":1516395,"text":"\"Companies hampered by old thinking won't be a problem"},{"time":1520541,"text":"because,\" he said,\" they simply won't be around long-term.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1526121,"text":"I've described not just a once-in-a-civilization"},{"time":1528985,"text":"business opportunity,"},{"time":1530592,"text":"but one of the most profound transitions"},{"time":1533015,"text":"in the history of our species."},{"time":1535531,"text":"We humans are inventing a new fire,"},{"time":1538954,"text":"not dug from below,"},{"time":1540698,"text":"but flowing from above;"},{"time":1543605,"text":"not scarce, but bountiful;"},{"time":1546536,"text":"not local, but everywhere;"},{"time":1548236,"text":"not transient, but permanent;"},{"time":1550867,"text":"not costly, but free."},{"time":1553767,"text":"And but for a little transitional tail of natural gas"},{"time":1557167,"text":"and a bit of biofuel grown in ways that sustain and endure,"},{"time":1560729,"text":"this new fire is flameless."},{"time":1564438,"text":"Efficiently used, it really can do our work"},{"time":1568502,"text":"without working our undoing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1571356,"text":"Each of you owns a piece of that $5 trillion prize."},{"time":1576238,"text":"And our new book \"Reinventing Fire\""},{"time":1578492,"text":"describes how you can capture it."},{"time":1580877,"text":"So with the conversation just begun"},{"time":1583146,"text":"at ReinventingFire.com,"},{"time":1585031,"text":"let me invite you each"},{"time":1587162,"text":"to engage with us and with each other, with everyone around you,"},{"time":1591000,"text":"to help make the world richer, fairer,"},{"time":1593792,"text":"cooler and safer"},{"time":1596400,"text":"by together reinventing fire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1599208,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1601067,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}